Berlusconi Survives First-Round Confidence Vote, Opposition Official Says

-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 
2011-10-14T12:07:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/berlusconi-survives-first-round-confidence-vote-opposition-official-says.html
Italian Prime Minister  Silvio
Berlusconi  won enough votes in the first round of balloting to
survive a confidence vote today in parliament, an opposition
official who attended the vote said.  Berlusconi won 315 votes in the first round, the party
official said. Lawmakers are still voting in the second round of
balloting.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Davis at 
 abdavis@bloomberg.net  